Text: This week started off being hectic already, with the second meeting being arranged up with Loic our project co-ordinator.
But unfortunately their company got hit with ransomware so we weren't able to meet till tuesday.
During the meeting alot of new terminology was being thrown around, I was barely catching up but luckily Gogo seems to be picking up on most of it so he could help us out afterwards.
Some of the things we got done during the meeting included downloading and setting up visual studio, and creating a branch of their source code for our project.
A problem we faced was that we were unable to make it onto landing page when running the code on local network, we identified the problem to be something related to their server.
So we have two options of working around this, we can either try to make a work around with our branched code or Loic was thinking he might be able to set up a server for us.

The goals that I had this week was to finish the proposal and do some researching on the material we will be using (node.js specifically), of course the proposal was finished and i think it went great.
I didnt do any research persay but i did look at source code to see how they implemented things, even if i dont know how that'll help me with this project hahaha.
Think next week ill need to focus on looking at the API and learning how to integrate it into our code then go from there, thus for next weeks goal i'll be hopefully getting the node.
js portion of the code working.
During the actual project proposal presentation i was super nervous especially since we were first, but after watching the other peoples one i bet i wouldve been even more nervous.
Since the scope and ambition of the others projects seem to be enormous.
If they were to actually give that to the clients i'd be super amazed.
Makes me think that our project maybe done in a shorter time frame and if so we might be able to work on something more for Loic!
